Let counter be number.
Let message be text.
Let numbers be number.
Let result be number.

Set counter to 0.
Set message to "Start of keyword test.".
Show message.

Get number ask "Enter a number:" storeInto numbers.

If numbers greaterThan 0 then:
    Show "Number is positive.".
    Increase counter by 1.
Otherwise if numbers lessThan 0 then:
    Show "Number is negative.".
    Increase counter by 1.
Otherwise:
    Show "Number is zero.".
    Set counter to counter plus 1.
    
Repeat 3 iterations:
    Show "Repeating test...".
    Increase counter by 1.

While counter lessThan 10:
    Increase counter by 2.
    Show counter.

Let list be text.
Set list to "A,B,C,D".

Foreach item in list:
    Show item.

Set result to remainderOf numbers dividedBy 2.
If result equalsTo 0 then:
    Show "Your number is even.".
Otherwise:
    Show "Your number is odd.".

To multiplyNumbers with a, b:
    Return a times b.

To greet with nan:
    Show "Hello from a no-parameter function.".

Set result to multiplyNumbers with (numbers, 5).
Show result.

greet with (nan).

Set message atPosition(1) to "X".
Show message.